The paper deals with the language recognition capabilities of quantum finite automata, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The undecidability results and complexity implications discussed in the paper are also relevant to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of measure many quantum finite automata and cutpoints suggests a connection to measure theory and probability theory, which are relevant to both logic (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also involves information theory, as it discusses the equivalence of languages recognized by different types of quantum finite automata (cs.IT).
